{"case_id": "nodejs-test-debugger-exec-timeout-v2-001", "context_method": "grep", "diagnoser": "real-agent-v1", "mode": "root_cause_diagnosis", "summary": "The test `parallel/test-debugger-exec` failed because the Node.js debugger client timed out (15000ms) while waiting for the initial break message matching `/break (?:on start )?in/i`. The debugger attached successfully but never emitted the expected break-on-start notification, causing `waitForInitialBreak` to throw a Timeout error.", "root_cause_category": "test_assertion", "root_cause": "test-debugger-exec timed out waiting for the debugger to emit a break-on-start message. The debugger connected and attached (output shows 'Debugger attached.') but the expected 'break ... in' line was never received within the 15000ms timeout, indicating the debugger did not pause at the initial breakpoint as expected.", "confidence": 0.92, "relevant_files": ["test/parallel/test-debugger-exec.js", "test/common/debugger.js"], "relevant_tests": ["parallel/test-debugger-exec"], "evidence": [{"quote": "Error: Timeout (15000) while waiting for /break (?:on start )?in/i", "reason": "Explicit timeout error thrown by the test helper after 15 seconds of waiting for the debugger break-on-start message that never arrived."}, {"quote": "at Object.waitForInitialBreak (/Users/runner/work/node/node/node/test/common/debugger.js:116:18)", "reason": "The stack trace shows the timeout originated in waitForInitialBreak, confirming the debugger never signalled the initial break."}, {"quote": "output: '< Debugger listening on ws://127.0.0.1:49508/1fd32687-38b3-450e-96e5-4a28a88f601e\\n' +\n    '< For help, see: https://nodejs.org/en/docs/inspector\\n' +\n    '< \\n' +\n    'connecting to 127.0.0.1:49508 ...\\n' +\n    ' ok\\n' +\n    '< Debugger attached.\\n'", "reason": "The debugger did connect and attach, but the output ends at 'debug> ' without any break-on-start message, confirming the expected pause never occurred."}, {"quote": "=== 1 tests fa